kubectl get <resource> - list resources
	Eg: kubectl get pods , kubectl get deployments , kubectl get services
kubectl describe - show detailed information about a resource
kubectl logs - print the logs from a container in a pod
kubectl exec - execute a command on a container in a pod
kubectl proxy - establish connection with a pod
kubectl describe <resource> 
	Eg: kubectl describe deployments/kubernetes-bootcamp


kubectl scale  - command, followed by the deployment type, name and desired number of instances: 
	Eg: $ kubectl scale deployments/kubernetes-bootcamp --replicas=4
